  "texts": [
    "This is exemplified by CasModaTest [99], which constructs a pool of high-quality code-test pair demonstrations and dynamically selects the most relevant examples based on code similarity to the method under test, thereby significantly improving the quality of the generated tests.Furthermore, irrespective of the chosen sample strategy, carefully crafted prompt templates and constraints serve as key techniques for stabilizing results and ensuring the generation of meaningful assertions.",
    "This is achieved through methods such as role-playing (e.g., adopting the persona of \"an expert Python Test-Driven Developer\" [9]) and the imposition of explicit quality constraints.",
    "These constraints range from simple requirements, such as mandating boundary value tests or timeout properties [58], to advanced reasoning structures like Chain-of-Thought (CoT) [99,143], which instructs the model to reason about test scenarios prior to code generation, thereby enhancing the logical robustness of the output.",
    "Advanced Prompting Techniques.While prompt composition supplies essential information, advanced techniques orchestrate these elements to enable deeper reasoning and self-correction in LLMs.",
    "These strategies are essential for overcoming the limitations associated with simple, single-pass generation.Chain-of-Thought (CoT) and Task Decomposition."
  ],
